{
  "_doc": "Strixhaven: School of Mages (STX) Draft + Collector recipes. The `draft` block is the original collation-derived recipe from data/_collation-facts/stx.json (The Collation Project) and is kept verbatim. The `collector` block was added from Wizards' official 'Collecting Strixhaven: School of Mages' article (https://magic.wizards.com/en/news/feature/collecting-strixhaven-school-mages-2021-03-25). STX (Apr 2021) is pre-Play-Booster, so there is intentionally NO play booster; Set Boosters are skipped per assignment. authoritative=true. Set composition (main set, excludes the 63 Mystical Archive cards): 105C / 80U / 69R / 21M. Sub-set codes: STX = main set, STA = Mystical Archive bonus sheet (Scryfall code 'sta'), C21 = Commander 2021 / Strixhaven Commander (the extended-art Commander slot), TSTX = tokens. Collector Booster = 16 (15 cards + 1 foil double-sided token): 1 foil-etched Mystical Archive uncommon, 1 foil-etched Mystical Archive rare/mythic, 1 traditional-foil Mystical Archive uncommon, 1 mixed traditional-foil slot (Mystical Archive rare/mythic OR foil extended-art main-set rare/mythic OR foil borderless mythic), 1 traditional-foil lesson, 1 extended-art/borderless rare/mythic (main set), 1 extended-art Commander rare/mythic, 1 traditional-foil rare/mythic, 2 traditional-foil uncommons, 5 traditional-foil commons, 1 foil token. The two foil-etched Archive cards are paired so one is always global art and one is the Japanese alternate art (modeled here as 50/50 japanese on each foil-etched slot). Article pool sizes used to DERIVE weights (exact percentages were not published): foil-etched Archive rare/mythic pool '30 rares / 15 mythic rares' -> 2:1 by count = 66.7% rare / 33.3% mythic. The mixed traditional-foil slot lists 'Mystical Archive global (45) + Mystical Archive Japanese alt-art (45) + foil extended-art main-set rares/mythics (81) + foil borderless mythics (9)' = 180 cards; weights are apportioned by those pool sizes (45/180, 45/180, 81/180, 9/180), with the 81 extended-art split rare:mythic by the main-set ~69R:21M ratio and the 90 Archive cards split uncommon/rare/mythic by the 18U:30R:15M Archive composition. Lesson slot: article states 6 boosters average ~5 common/uncommon lessons + 1 rare/mythic lesson (modeled 70/20/10 common/uncommon/rare like the draft lesson slot, matching the kept draft block). Approximations: Japanese alternate-art uses the japanese filter; foil-etched uses etched_foil; borderless planeswalker / borderless Elder Dragon use the borderless filter; showcase/extended-art booster-fun uses extended_art; lessons use the lesson filter.",

